===Etymology===
From ancient Greek [[Μακεδονία]] (''Makedonia'') "highland", from ancient Greek [[μακεδνός]] (''makednos'')  "high, tall", from Doric Greek [[μάκος]] (''makos'') "height, length" . In Ionian Greek: [[μήκος]] (''mekos'').
In Greek mythology [[Μακεδονία]] (''Makedonia'') was named after [[Μακεδών]] (''Makedon''), the forefather of the Macedonians, son of [[Ζεύς]] (''Zeus'') and [[Πανδώρα]] (''Pandora''). ([[Pandora]] was the sister of Έλλην ''Hellen'', the forefather of  [[Έλληνες]] ''Hellenes'', "Greeks".)

